{
    "Implementation approach": "We will build a lightweight monolithic web application using Python Flask for the server, SQLAlchemy with SQLite for persistence, and APScheduler for background tasks (auto-expiry and reservation release). The frontend uses Jinja2 templates with Bootstrap for a clean responsive dashboard. The system exposes RESTful endpoints for inventory and request management while serving a server-rendered dashboard. For simplicity and easy deployment, we avoid heavy frontend frameworks. The complex matching algorithm is implemented in a dedicated service module, ensuring ACID compliance through database transactions.",
    "File list": [
        "main.py",
        "config.py",
        "app/models.py",
        "app/routes.py",
        "app/matching_service.py",
        "app/scheduler.py",
        "app/forms.py",
        "templates/base.html",
        "templates/dashboard.html",
        "templates/inventory.html",
        "templates/requests.html",
        "templates/alerts.html",
        "static/css/style.css",
        "static/js/main.js"
    ],
    "Data structures and interfaces": "```mermaid\nclassDiagram\n    class BloodUnit {\n        +int id\n        +str abo_type\n        +str rh_factor\n        +datetime collection_date\n        +datetime expiry_date\n        +str status: 'available','reserved','issued','expired'\n        +int? reservation_id\n        +__init__(abo_type, rh_factor, collection_date)\n        +expire()\n        +reserve(request_id) -> bool\n        +issue() -> bool\n        +release() -> bool\n    }\n    class TransfusionRequest {\n        +int id\n        +str abo_type\n        +str rh_factor\n        +int quantity\n        +str status: 'pending','fulfilled','cancelled'\n        +datetime created_at\n        +list[BloodUnit] matched_units\n        +__init__(abo_type, rh_factor, quantity)\n        +fulfill()\n        +cancel()\n    }\n    class Reservation {\n        +int id\n        +int request_id\n        +int unit_id\n        +datetime reserved_at\n        +bool confirmed\n        +release_after() datetime\n        +confirm()\n        +expire()\n    }\n    class StockAlert {\n        +int id\n        +str abo_type\n        +str rh_factor\n        +int current_stock\n        +datetime created_at\n        +bool active\n        +resolve()\n    }\n    class MatchingService {\n        +find_compatible_units(abo_type, rh_factor, quantity) -> list[BloodUnit]\n        +reserve_units(request, units)\n        +auto_match_and_reserve(request) -> bool\n    }\n    class Scheduler {\n        +expire_units_job()\n        +release_unconfirmed_reservations()\n        +check_and_raise_alerts()\n    }\n    class DashboardData {\n        +list[dict] stock_summary\n        +list[BloodUnit] expiring_soon\n        +list[TransfusionRequest] open_requests\n        +list[StockAlert] active_alerts\n    }\n    BloodUnit --> Reservation : has one\n    TransfusionRequest --> Reservation : has many\n    MatchingService --> BloodUnit\n    MatchingService --> TransfusionRequest\n    MatchingService --> Reservation\n    Scheduler --> BloodUnit\n    Scheduler --> Reservation\n    Scheduler --> StockAlert\n```\n",
    "Program call flow": "```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Admin as Administrator\n    participant UI as Web UI (Flask)\n    participant M as Main (app.py)\n    participant DB as SQLite Database\n    participant Sched as APScheduler\n\n    Admin ->> UI: Submit new blood unit form\n    UI ->> M: POST /inventory/add (abo_type, rh, collection_date)\n    M ->> DB: INSERT BloodUnit\n    DB -->> M: unit saved\n    M -->> UI: redirect with success message\n\n    Nurse ->> UI: Submit transfusion request\n    UI ->> M: POST /requests/new (abo_type, rh, quantity)\n    M ->> M: MatchingService.auto_match_and_reserve(request)\n    M ->> DB: SELECT compatible units (exact type first, then closest expiry)\n    DB -->> M: units list\n    M ->> DB: INSERT Reservation rows for each matched unit\n    M ->> DB: UPDATE BloodUnit status='reserved'\n    M ->> DB: UPDATE Request status='pending' (if partial) or 'fulfilled'\n    M ->> DB: SELECT current stock per type\n    M ->> M: check if any stock < 5 → create StockAlert\n    M -->> UI: redirect to dashboard\n\n    Sched ->> M: run expire_units_job (every hour)\n    M ->> DB: SELECT units where expiry_date < now and status='available' or 'reserved'\n    M ->> DB: UPDATE BloodUnit status='expired'\n\n    Sched ->> M: run release_unconfirmed_reservations (every 10 minutes)\n    M ->> DB: SELECT reservations where reserved_at < now - 24h and confirmed=False\n    M ->> DB: UPDATE BloodUnit status='available', DELETE reservation\n\n    Sched ->> M: run check_and_raise_alerts (every 5 minutes)\n    M ->> DB: SELECT count(*) per type/rh where status='available'\n    M ->> M: compare with threshold 5, create alerts if needed\n    DB -->> M: alert inserted\n\n    Manager ->> UI: GET /dashboard\n    UI ->> M: GET /dashboard\n    M ->> DB: aggregate stock by type, units expiring in 7 days, pending requests, active alerts\n    DB -->> M: data\n    M -->> UI: render dashboard.html with dashboard data\n```\n",
    "Anything UNCLEAR": "Clarification needed on Rh compatibility rules. Standard transfusion practice: Rh-negative can only receive Rh-negative blood; Rh-positive can receive Rh-positive or Rh-negative. However, the requirement states 'standard ABO/Rh donor compatibility' – we will implement exactly that. Also, the alert mechanism is currently dashboard-based; future integrations (email/SMS) can be added as separate services. User authentication and role-based access (admin, nurse, technician) are not explicitly requested but would be necessary for a production system; we assume they are out of scope for this version, but the architecture allows easy integration of Flask-Login later."
}
[/CONTENT]
